piece1_23.ex1_description: The two musical cues under investigation are tempo and rhythmic unit. ... According to the arousal-mood hypothesis, listening to music affects ... the music pieces for the following indirect semantic scales, where each scale is ..... level of valence and arousal, or at a neutral level of one or both of these factors.
piece1_23.ex2_arousal: Valence is positive or negative affectivity, whereas arousal measures how calming or exciting the information is. ... That's the mark of high-arousal emotions. Valence codes emotional events as positive or negative. Arousal comes from our reptilian brain.Valence, as used in psychology, especially in discussing emotions, means the intrinsic attractiveness/"good"-ness (positive valence) or averseness/"bad"-ness (negative valence) of an event, object, or situation. The term also characterizes and categorizes specific emotions. ... Joy has positive valence.

piece99_9.ex1_description: The piece is fast paced, creating excitement but the tone of the piece is in minor so it also creates a tense, and sad timbre.
piece99_9.ex2_arousal: This piece is more in the minor tones, with a sad but optimistic tone to it. It has a slightly tense and frustrated quality to it.

piece9_1.ex1_description: the piece changed from dark/deliberate to jaunty very suddenly. So it became more positive and even more intense.
piece9_1.ex2_arousal: the music seemed to stay within a confined zone of valence and arousal.

piece9_10.ex1_description: The music increased in sound.  It was nice.
piece9_10.ex2_arousal: It went up and down interchangeably.  It would have sounded good if it was a little lower in the sound.

piece9_11.ex1_description: Sounds somber at first, then all excited. Valence and arousal definitely fluctuates
piece9_11.ex2_arousal: Sounds like game music. Engaging. The valence and arousal don't change considerably

piece9_12.ex1_description: music volume decreased initially.  there was a tempo change with increased volume.
piece9_12.ex2_arousal: music was consistent. I did not perceive any changes.

piece9_13.ex1_description: Like a jazz improvisation, this music picks up. It gains in speed and tempo both.
piece9_13.ex2_arousal: While increasing in both categories it doesn't increase much. It does seem a bit lighter and heartier as it goes on.

piece9_14.ex1_description: The music initially decreased in valence. After four seconds, the valence and arousal both increased.
piece9_14.ex2_arousal: The valence and arousal of the piece remained relatively constant throughout. I would rate the piece as having negative valence. The arousal however was intense.

piece9_15.ex1_description: The valence went from really negative to a high positive. The arousal was mild and stayed mild. It never increased to an intense level.
piece9_15.ex2_arousal: Both the valence and arousal stayed the same. In my opinion, there were no huge noticeable changes in either.

piece9_16.ex1_description: Slow and upbeat into chipper, bouncy, and fun.
piece9_16.ex2_arousal: exploratory, adventurous. looking for something or precautionary.

piece9_17.ex1_description: At first the piece was easy going and it felt like I was about to become delighted. Then it became depressing. Then it was merely content.
piece9_17.ex2_arousal: It kept a steady flow of emotions. I felt calm during the duration.

piece9_18.ex1_description: from upbeat and peppy to upbeat with an evil negative undertone
piece9_18.ex2_arousal: pretty much the same mildness throughout the song

piece9_19.ex1_description: the piece seemed to intensify as it was playing.
piece9_19.ex2_arousal: I didn't notice any real change while the piece was playing.

piece9_2.ex1_description: It started off happy and light and kinda went dark and tense.
piece9_2.ex2_arousal: It sound happy to me. Like the composer enjoyed making this piece.

piece9_20.ex1_description: i felt intrigued by the beginning then felt more intense yet not in a positive way
piece9_20.ex2_arousal: I feel happier more positive when the piece does not be repetitive

piece9_22.ex1_description: Delighted. Feeling joyful. Brought back to western style saloon era.
piece9_22.ex2_arousal: Feeling excited. Feelings of motivation and anticipation. Almost anthem like to gain energy and to get gain momentum.

piece9_24.ex1_description: Started slow and a little depressing then picked up the pace and became cheerful
piece9_24.ex2_arousal: This piece seemed pretty content and the mood was steady

piece9_25.ex1_description: Starts off a bit slow, then the tempo increases and it gets faster and more energetic.
piece9_25.ex2_arousal: It is a pretty negative valence but as it goes on it grows more positive. The arousal goes from slightly mild to slightly intense.

piece9_26.ex1_description: a whimsical beginning down to a gradient melancholy back to a fair like atmosphere

piece9_27.ex2_arousal:
Tensed to Happy tone.
Sad to relaxed.

piece9_28.ex1_description: When the song starts it has sad overtones. Then it picks up and makes me feel energized.
piece9_28.ex2_arousal: Went from feeling uplifting to more serious.

piece9_29.ex1_description: This example made me tense and a little excited.
piece9_29.ex2_arousal: I recognize this music from a video game. It made me very happy.

piece9_3.ex2_arousal: tone became more mild. also more pleasant, positive.

piece9_4.ex1_description: At first it is like a neutral to negative feel. Then all of a sudden there is a moment of intenseness.
piece9_4.ex2_arousal: It seems to have a normal consistent pace. It's arousal seems to fall towards a somewhat mild and content feel.

piece9_5.ex1_description: It started off slowly but happy and then built in speed and noise level.
piece9_5.ex2_arousal: Seemed to remain consistent almost like it was in the middle of the song.  I might be able to tell more if it was longer

piece9_6.ex1_description: This starts off a certain way then changes in a slightly strange way. It is interesting and I wanted to know how the rest of the music plays out.
piece9_6.ex2_arousal: This is nostalgic because I recognize this and know what it's from. I feel more delighted than before and curious as well. It makes me want to listen to more music.

piece9_7.ex1_description: The piece begins slow in tempo and then becomes faster, making it sound more intense. The upbeat tempo helps it sound more positive despite sounding in a minor key.
piece9_7.ex2_arousal: The beginning rhythm sounds suspenseful, making it sound intense. As the melody comes in, it sounds more major, therefore positive. It also sounds more grounded, making it seem less intense.

piece9_8.ex2_arousal: I feel it stayed the same

piece9_9.ex1_description: the music is kind of happy and then starts slowing down. it then picks up and gives off the impression it is happy/excited
piece9_9.ex2_arousal: this music sounds intense. it doesn't change much but it ends very strong
